“There is a housing crisis and an overwhelming need for affordable housing and it’s critical that people are able to live in a home that they can afford,” he said.
The NMG CEO noted that financial institutions prefer the salaried formal sector, to the disadvantage of the informal sector individuals.
“Financing has also been made harder as institutions prefer to finance projects that they have been involved in throughout the project, ignoring upcoming developers who are embracing low cost methods of construction,” he said. He allegedly received a sh200,000 bribe to approve the opening of a fuel station in Oyugis. Council of Governors chair Wycliffe Oparanya urges medics to quickly resolve issues with concerned counties. He allegedly received a sh200,000 bribe to approve the opening of a fuel station in Oyugis. Kabila had succeeded in forming an army with many generals said to still be loyal to him. This is the first time Uhuru is meeting Abiy since Addis Ababa launched a crackdown on TPLF.